      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 48,
      "message": "The server is case-sensitive. e.g. a GET to /rics works but a GET to /RiCs does not work (404). The paths provided will have to match the endpoints in terms of case. So, although a call to RiCs gives a 404, it will get past the exclusion filter and be logged by ReactiveEntryExitFilter because it is  /RiCs and not /rics. Is there a further change you recommend here?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7603,
        "name": "Saul Gill",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "saul.gill@est.tech",
        "username": "saul.gill"
      },
      "updated": "2025-06-06 08:37:26.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "f1fd3bdf_329df13d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
